The paper proposes a design of memory augmented neural networks (MANNs) for online adaptation in classification models. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also demonstrates significant accuracy gains on various tasks including word-modelling and few-shot learning, which are common tasks in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks, which is a common topic in neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.CL, cs.CV, and cs.NE.
